ji3mVCR6-rYIUJEBSpSi_E-NbUlG31bGT-mae5b8XI9b3AYA68ldVMs8th&_nc_zt=23&_nc_ht=scontent-bos5-1.xx&_nc_gid=KlzWNHYM9g_8fIIfhbkWXQ&_nc_ss=7a389&oh=00_Af1EqPmS1RvI8jcQQzS3TIw9ugwq98FzWQZoYcgdIV78yg&oe=69EEADBC","moreInfo":"https://www.digitalcommonwealth.org/search?coordinates=%5B42.33310928934594%2C-71.05750825003575+TO+42.33869261113705%2C-71.04915048674536%5D&f%5Bgenre_basic_ssim%5D%5B%5D=Photographs&page=3&spatial_search_type=bbox&view=gallery","id":"15"},{"type":"geoMap","tileJSON":"https://tiles.arcgis.com/tiles/hGdibHYSPO59RG1h/arcgis/rest/services/BW_Orthos_Tile_Package/MapServer/tile/{z}/{y}/{x}","moreInfo":"https://tiles.arcgis.com/tiles/hGdibHYSPO59RG1h/arcgis/rest/services/BW_Orthos_Tile_Package/MapServer/tile/{z}/{y}/{x}","id":"16"},{"type":"staticImage","imageFile":"https://scontent-bos5-1.xx.fbcdn.net/v/t39.30808-6/649202715_26250425614595438_7876993460669062923_n.jpg?_nc_cat=107&ccb=1-7&_nc_sid=e06c5d&_nc_ohc=xBd5eT9gsAYQ7kNvwGBTnPt&_nc_oc=Adprn-X2xNCniAvjdNXV6tdlhQOZGg5CM0rAEFiMI8tYG5AaaPqTgTSVncdv2yJFnG1O8JPoWZHbO8vnZo4CwIwY&_nc_zt=23&_nc_ht=scontent-bos5-1.xx&_nc_gid=3tUlZsutn0SXH20zcU6iDw&_nc_ss=7a389&oh=00_Af0jYWhy1T4ooMQpKM5fBIUWP1PNRgBkafIDZWzoLsduWg&oe=69EEBB25","moreInfo":"https://www.facebook.com/photo/?fbid=9491675957563667&set=gm.1988822308312196&idorvanity=560423297818778","id":"17"}],"scenes":[{"caption":{"text":"In 1949, the final brick was placed in the West Broadway Housing Development, offering homes to families of veterans returning from the war effort. Originally designated for white residents alone, this would be the first of four iterations of public housing in this South Boston neighborhood. The city would not desegregate the project until the 1960s, and while situated in the same neighborhood, the tenants of the West Broadway Homes today are very diverse.","title":"West Broadway Today"},"source":"2","timestamp":null,"extent":[-7909918.582978349,5211571.801422004,-7909334.033979002,5212152.032348408],"moreInfo":"https://s3.us-east-2.wasabisys.com/urbanatlases/al88svmi0/tileset.json"},{"caption":{"text":"The partial land clearing of this neighborhood, bordered by D Street, B Street, West Broadway, and West Seventh Street, would begin in 1941, with great focus placed on D street in particular...","title":"D Street "},"source":"2","timestamp":null,"extent":[-7909599.831727297,5211585.933756973,-7909344.447050129,5211866.249648478],"moreInfo":"https://s3.us-east-2.wasabisys.com/urbanatlases/al88svmi0/tileset.json"},{"caption":{"text":"largely due to the heavy concentration of dilapidates buildings seen in the first half of the twentieth century. The first iteration of the West Broadway Homes would be colloquially known as the \"D Street Projects\". ","title":"D Street"},"source":"3","timestamp":null,"extent":"fit","moreInfo":"https://www.digitalcommonwealth.org/search?coordinates=%5B42.33693570408431%2C-71.05770255541643%20TO%2042.34127822334554%2C-71.05120183777767%5D&spatial_search_type=bbox&view=gallery&f%5Bgenre_basic_ssim%5D%5B%5D=Photographs"},{"caption":{"text":"This 1960 map shows the perceptions of South Boston through the middle of the twentieth century, deeming neighborhoods as either \"deteriorating\", \"deteriorated\", or \"renewal area\". The conditions depicted on this map are a far cry from what city planners had envisioned when the land which would become Boston's South End was first filled.","title":"South End Renewal"},"source":"1","timestamp":null,"extent":"fit","moreInfo":"https://thewestendmuseum.org/history/era/new-boston/south-enders-vs-the-b-r-a-urban-renewal-in-bostons-south-end/"},{"caption":{"text":"The tidal marshes of south of Boston's downtown would be filled in through the first half of the 19th century with the intention of providing homes for the city's wealthier residents. Yet growing industrial infrastructure, and the construction of the railroad depicted here, would drive property values down leading to a mass emigration of wealth. Wealth would be replaced with low rents and immigrant residents.","title":"The Beginnings of the South End"},"source":"2","timestamp":null,"extent":[-7909960.958524486,5211898.002323327,-7909738.0869159335,5212233.746119794],"moreInfo":"https://s3.us-east-2.wasabisys.com/urbanatlases/al88svmi0/tileset.json"}]}
